<!-- ROW 3: RULES + BEHAVIORAL + OVERNIGHT -->
<div class="grid">

  <!-- MECHANICAL RULES -->
  <div class="sec">
    <div class="sec-title">Mechanical Rules</div>
    <div class="rule"><div class="rule-num">R1</div><div class="rule-txt"><strong>Acceptance = close above/below level.</strong> Wick only = not accepted. 5-min close minimum to confirm.</div></div>
    <div class="rule"><div class="rule-num">R2</div><div class="rule-txt"><strong>T3/T4 entry window: 9:30–2:30 PM.</strong> 14.2 avg pullbacks per T3 day after 8am. Any retrace to OB/FVG/PDH is valid.</div></div>
    <div class="rule"><div class="rule-num">R3</div><div class="rule-txt"><strong>First pullback averages 68pts.</strong> Don't use a 20pt stop on a T3 day. Normal retrace = 40–70pts.</div></div>
    <div class="rule"><div class="rule-num">R4</div><div class="rule-txt"><strong>Highest cont% on T3 = pullbacks #3–#8</strong> (11am–1:30pm). 80–83% continuation. Miss #1 → wait for #3.</div></div>
    <div class="rule"><div class="rule-num">R5</div><div class="rule-txt"><strong>T3+T1 same day = max conviction.</strong> London accepted PDH at 8am, KZ confirmed at 11am. Two institutional confirmations.</div></div>
    <div class="rule"><div class="rule-num">R6</div><div class="rule-txt"><strong>No trade after 3pm.</strong> Continuation rate drops to 54% on T3 days. 55% on T4. Risk/reward gone.</div></div>
    <div class="rule"><div class="rule-num">R7</div><div class="rule-txt"><strong>Failed T3 is a bear signal.</strong> London wicked PDH+rejected → watch for BD5+score3 at 11am → T7 fires (92.3% WR).</div></div>
  </div>

  <!-- OVERNIGHT CONTEXT -->
  <div class="sec">
    <div class="sec-title">Overnight Bias Checklist (pre-9:30)</div>
    <div class="rule"><div class="rule-num">→</div><div class="rule-txt"><strong>8:00 AM:</strong> London close above PDH = T3. Below PDL = T4. Inside = wait for 11am.</div></div>
    <div class="rule"><div class="rule-num">→</div><div class="rule-txt"><strong>9:29 AM pre close location:</strong><br>
      Above PDH = 76% bull day · Above 75% = 62% bull<br>
      Below PDL = 75% bear day · Below 25% = 63% bear</div></div>
    <div class="rule"><div class="rule-num">→</div><div class="rule-txt"><strong>Asia accepted PDH</strong> (closed above) = 63.6% bull. Asia rejected PDH (wick) = coin flip alone — wait for London.</div></div>
    <div class="rule"><div class="rule-num">→</div><div class="rule-txt"><strong>Triple confirmation (strongest):</strong> Asia acc PDH + London above PDH + Pre above PDH = 88% bull displacement at 9:30.</div></div>
    <div class="rule"><div class="rule-num">→</div><div class="rule-txt"><strong>Asia + London agree direction:</strong> Both bull = 61.3% bull day. Both bear = 40.2% bull. They disagree = coin flip — stand down.</div></div>
    <div class="rule"><div class="rule-num">→</div><div class="rule-txt"><strong>Asia rej PDH + Pre above PDH</strong> = 76% bull day. Today's displacement setup — Pre holding above PDH is the key tell.</div></div>
  </div>

  <!-- BEHAVIORAL RISKS + SIZE -->
  <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:10px">

    <div class="sec red">
      <div class="sec-title">Behavioral Risks — Never Do These</div>
      <div class="rule"><div class="rule-num">✗</div><div class="rule-txt"><strong>FOMO</strong> — entering after the move. 14 pullbacks per day. Wait for the next one.</div></div>
      <div class="rule"><div class="rule-num">✗</div><div class="rule-txt"><strong>Oversizing T5/T6/T7/T8</strong> — half-size tiers exist because external level wasn't confirmed.</div></div>
      <div class="rule"><div class="rule-num">✗</div><div class="rule-txt"><strong>Trading no-signal days</strong> — if no tier fires, the model says no edge. Close the platform.</div></div>
      <div class="rule"><div class="rule-num">✗</div><div class="rule-txt"><strong>Adding indicators</strong> — every condition is price-based. Indicators add noise and create doubt.</div></div>
      <div class="rule"><div class="rule-num">✗</div><div class="rule-txt"><strong>Entering after 3pm</strong> — HOD/LOD already forming. Continuation at 54%.</div></div>
    </div>

    <div class="sec">
      <div class="sec-title">Size Rules</div>
      <div class="row"><span class="rl">T1 + T2 (BU2★+BU5★ or BD2★+BD5★)</span><span class="rv g">Full</span></div>
      <div class="row"><span class="rl">T3 + T4 (London accepted PDH/PDL)</span><span class="rv g">Full</span></div>
      <div class="row"><span class="rl">T5 + T6 (score 3+, no external level)</span><span class="rv a">Half</span></div>
      <div class="row"><span class="rl">T7 + T8 (failed T3/T4 + confirmed)</span><span class="rv a">Half</span></div>
      <div class="row"><span class="rl">KZ did not expand overnight range</span><span class="rv a">Half any tier</span></div>
      <div class="row" style="border:none"><span class="rl">Tuesday + Friday</span><span class="rv g">Full + wider target</span></div>
    </div>

    <div class="sec amber">
      <div class="sec-title">Stop &amp; Target Guidelines</div>
      <div class="row"><span class="rl">Hard stop</span><span class="rv">Below/above OB entry level</span></div>
      <div class="row"><span class="rl">T3/T4 stop reference</span><span class="rv">Below London Low / above London High</span></div>
      <div class="row"><span class="rl">Target 1</span><span class="rv">25–50pts · close 50%</span></div>
      <div class="row"><span class="rl">Target 2</span><span class="rv">Prior swing / PDH / PDL</span></div>
      <div class="row"><span class="rl">T3 day avg first pullback</span><span class="rv">68pts deep — size stop accordingly</span></div>
      <div class="row" style="border:none"><span class="rl">T4 day avg first counter-rally</span><span class="rv">95pts — wider stop on shorts</span></div>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>

